h3. Removing text with an inline comment, should cause the comment to be deleted in mobile
h3. Environment
Confluence Mobile

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create an inline comment
 # Delete the text that the comment was highlighting
 # View in mobile

h3. Expected Results
The comment should not be visible with the other comments
h3. Actual Results
The comment is visible, and appears current.

h3. Notes
I think this is due to the different status for resolved versus dangling. A comment that has been resolved due to text being deleted has a resolution as dangling. To make mobile consistent with the web, this comment should not appear with the other comments.

{code}
extensions: {
   location: "inline",
   resolution: {
   status: "resolved"
   }
}
{code}

{code}
extensions: {
  location: "inline",
  resolution: {
    status: "dangling"
  }
}
{code}

h3. Workaround
Delete the comment with the rest api, there is no way in web or mobile for a customer to delete this dangling comment through the UI.

cc [~ametcalfe]

h3. Summary
Apps using {{webItems}} module returns a 404 when clicked.  

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a connect app with a web item for example {code}"webItems": [
  {
    "key": "hello-world-page-confluence",
    "location": "system.header/left",
    "name": {
        "value": "AC WEBITEM EDIT"
    },
    "url": "/hello-world-test",
    "conditions": [{
        "condition": "user_is_logged_in"
    }]
}{code}

h3. Expected Results
Clicking the web item will go to the indicated URL.

h3. Actual Results
A preceding {{https://hostUrl/wiki}} is added to the URL like 
{code}
https://iangil.atlassian.net/wikihttps://iangil.atlassian.net/wiki/plugins/servlet/ac-redirect/my-app/hello-world-page-confluence?user.key=8a7f80835fdcfe63015fffebde&user.id=admin?view=addons
{code}

h3. Notes
* A probable regression of https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-66642
* Resulted in some of the vendors' app functionalities to not work or inaccessible

h3. Workaround
Currently, there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available.

h3. Summary

When defining webItems with icons on them:

{code}
   "webItems":[
      {
         "key":"web-item-export-office-launcher",
         "name":{
            "value":"Export to Word"
         },
         "icon":{
            "width":16,
            "height":16,
            "url":"/static/assets/images/office/OFCE_white_16px.svg"
         },
         "url":"/static/index.html",
         "location":"system.content.action/secondary",
         "context":"addon",
         "target":{
            "type":"dialog",
            "options":{
               "chrome":false,
               "height":"100%",
               "width":"100%"
            }
         },
         "styleClasses":[
            "webitem",
            "system-present-webitem"
         ],
         "tooltip":{
            "value":"Export"
         }
      }
   ]
{code}

no icon is displayed on side of it:

 !Screen Shot 2019-05-23 at 10.46.17.png|thumbnail! 
 !Screen Shot 2019-05-24 at 1.45.43 PM.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Impact
Apps affected by this:
* Scroll PDF Exporter on Confluence
* Scroll Word Exporter on Confluence
* Content Exporter

