h3. Issue Summary

When a web-item definition as such:
{code}
{
            "key": "sys-header-left",
            "location": "system.header/left",
            "context": "addon",
            "name":
            {
              "value": "Anne System Header Left"
            },
            "url": "/hello-world?app=jira&accountId={user.accountId}",
            "conditions": [
              {
                "condition": "user_is_logged_in"
              }
            ],
            "tooltip": {
              "value": "Anne Wizard"
            },
            "target": {
              "type": "dialog",
              "options": {
                "width": "840px",
                "height": "373px"
              }
            }
          }
{code}
with a dialog target, a 404 page is displayed instead of loading it in a dialog

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# In a connect app, add a webItem definition like above
# Go to your instance and access app's webItem
# You'll be redirected to a 404: https://monosnap.com/file/E8ap8EgoIpE2KpOZKSPYN5Tt1mYiYU
 [^anne-replication-404.webm] 

h3. Expected Results
App details loaded in a dialog

h3. Actual Results
Redirected to 404

h3. Notes
* Seems to work in Jira

h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
